{"key":"post-8647517","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8647517</id>\n<content>It matters little how much water is in the PC as long as it doesn't run dry.&amp;nbsp; If the jars are on a shelf and you're starting the run with everything at room temperature, it sounds like a load of crappy jars.&amp;nbsp; I've probably had five jars in the last twenty years crack while in the PC, so the problem is rare indeed.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Make sure you're not doing anything to cool the PC down after the cooking cycle other than simply shutting off the stove.&amp;nbsp; If you pop the weight to let out steam, that's the problem.&amp;nbsp; They need to heat slowly, and then cool slowly.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8647580</next>\n<prev>8646994</prev>\n<first>8646829</first>\n<last>8655088</last>\n<when>1216329538</when>\n<utime>07/18/08 12:18 AM</utime>\n</post>"}